<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>7868</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0030</addr>  <route>jms-0030.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>3</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Category with representable maps</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>category with representable maps</em> or <em>CwR</em> is defined by <link href="uemura-2021-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Abstract and Concrete Type Theories">Uemura</link> to be a category <tex>\mathcal{C}</tex> with finite limits equipped with a pullback-stable class <tex>\mathrm{R} _{ \mathcal{C} } \subseteq   \mathbf{hom} _{ \mathcal{C} }</tex> of <link href="jms-0031.xml" type="local" title="Exponentiable arrow">exponentiable arrows</link> in <tex>\mathcal{C}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>7869</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0031</addr>  <route>jms-0031.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>3</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Exponentiable arrow</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="jms-0033.xml" type="local" title="Carrable map">carrable map</link> <tex>{ E } \xrightarrow{p} { B }</tex> in a category <tex>\mathcal{C}</tex> is said to be <em>exponentiable</em> when it is <link href="jms-0032.xml" type="local" title="Exponentiable object">exponentiable</link> when viewed as an object of the slice category <tex>{ \mathcal{C} } _{ / B }</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>7870</anchor> <taxon>Reference</